    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hi, i'm buying my first house and i'm a bit confused. what exactly is escrow? like where does my earnest money actually go after i sign the contract and before we close?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Congratulations on your new home purchase. Escrow is a separate account held by a third party, typically an escrow agent or the title company, that holds and manages money and documents until certain conditions are met, such as closing. The earnest money deposit you put down when you sign the contract is usually placed into escrow. This foundational deposit often gets applied to prepaid interest, closing costs, and other charges, which are deducted once the property belongs to you.",
