      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The person or company responsible for managing the escrow account is usually an independent escrow agent or title company, often with the assistance of a real estate attorney. They are bound by state and local regulations to ensure the funds' deposit and management are secure and separate from their operations. You can rest assured that the funds can be accessed and returned to you if there's a dispute or you change your mind, with many escrow services offering protection and guarantees to safeguard your deposit.",
